{"findings":[{"id":"F-001","severity":"Critical","confidence":"high","title":"Public `calcStepIncome` lets any player mint arbitrary withdrawable rewards","locations":["0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:285","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:305","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:855","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:866","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:868","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:869"],"claim":"`calcStepIncome` is `public` and performs no authorization or caller-context checks, so any externally owned account can credit `stepIncome` and `totalSettled` for any PID up to that PID's `playBiggertReward`. Those forged earnings are then withdrawable through `withdraw()`. Because the function also decrements `mainPoolBalance` without checking pool sufficiency, oversized calls can additionally corrupt pool accounting via underflow.","impact":"An attacker can join once, mint themselves rewards they never earned, and withdraw real ETH from `mainPoolWithdrawBalance`. This is a permissionless drain of the round's withdrawable liquidity, with additional accounting corruption if `mainPoolBalance` is driven below zero.","paths":["Join the game to obtain an active PID and a nonzero `playBiggertReward` cap.","Call `calcStepIncome(attackerPid, attackerChosenValue, attackerChosenDividend)` directly until `totalSettled` reaches the desired forged amount.","Call `withdraw()` to convert the fabricated balance into ETH from the round's withdrawable pool."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-002","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"The final-withdraw branch zeroes the round balance before paying, permanently orphaning current-round claims","locations":["0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:287","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:295","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:296","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:297","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:298","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:299"],"claim":"When a caller's payout reaches the round remainder, `withdraw()` takes the `totalWdBal >= mainPoolWithdrawBalance[RID]` branch, sets `mainPoolWithdrawBalance[RID] = 0`, and then records/transfers `mainPoolWithdrawBalance[RID]`, which is now zero. The caller receives nothing, while the round's withdraw gate is permanently shut for that RID.","impact":"Any user whose claim is at least the remaining withdrawable balance can zero the round's withdrawal balance without receiving the funds. Current-round settled rewards then become unwithdrawable forever because future `withdraw()` calls require a positive `mainPoolWithdrawBalance[RID]`, while withdrawals for old rounds are never supported.","paths":["Accrue a withdrawable amount at least as large as the current `mainPoolWithdrawBalance[RID]`.","Call `withdraw()` while that amount is still greater than or equal to the remaining round balance.","The function zeroes `mainPoolWithdrawBalance[RID]` first, transfers 0 wei, and blocks all later withdrawals for that round."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-003","severity":"High","confidence":"high","title":"Any joiner can reactivate arbitrary dormant accounts and restore their old earning rights","locations":["0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:216","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:217","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:546","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:550","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:552","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:553","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:554","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:331","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:333","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:345"],"claim":"For existing or new non-VIP joiners, `joinGame()` passes the caller-supplied `parentAddr` into `activeParent()`. If that referenced PID is inactive in the current round, `activeParent()` reactivates it and restores its unfinished prior-round `playBiggertReward`, `ticketInCost`, and `lastCalcSITime` without requiring that account to buy into the new round. The revived account can then use the restored `ticketInCost` and historical settlement timestamp to resume earning and withdrawing from the current round.","impact":"Attackers can revive colluding or dormant accounts that did not fund the current round, letting them earn fresh rewards against new-round liquidity using old-round state. This siphons value from honest entrants and undermines the round reset model.","paths":["Wait for a target PID with unfinished prior-round reward capacity to be inactive in the new round.","Call `joinGame(targetAddr)` from any non-VIP EOA with at least 10 ETH so `activeParent()` is reached.","The target PID is reactivated with restored reward cap and settlement state, then its owner calls earning/withdrawal functions to extract current-round funds without paying the current-round ticket."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-004","severity":"High","confidence":"medium","title":"Hardcoded VIP addresses receive a built-in 20,000x reward-cap backdoor","locations":["0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:161","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:565","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:615","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:616","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:953"],"claim":"The contract hardcodes a fixed set of privileged VIP EOAs. When one of those addresses joins, `checkTicket()` calls `initVip()`, binds it to a reserved PID, and credits `playBiggertReward += value * 20000`, while ordinary users only receive 2x to 3x caps.","impact":"Control of any hardcoded VIP key allows extraction rights that are orders of magnitude larger than the deposited principal, creating an embedded privileged drain path that can render the pool insolvent and redirect ordinary-user funds to the VIP set.","paths":["Control one of the hardcoded VIP EOAs.","Call `joinGame()` from that address so `checkTicket()` routes through VIP initialization.","Receive a 20,000x reward ceiling and monetize it against later pool inflows through the normal earning and withdrawal paths."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]},{"id":"F-005","severity":"Medium","confidence":"high","title":"The last insurance claimant can lose the entire residual payout because the pool is zeroed before the assignment","locations":["0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:258","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:259","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:260","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:261","0xde46fcf6ab7559e4355b8ee3d7fba0f2730cddd8/Contract.sol:268"],"claim":"For non-final lucky users, `withdraw()` computes `bunlers = ticketInCost * 2`. If that exceeds the remaining `insePoolBalance[RID-1]`, the code first sets `insePoolBalance[RID-1] = 0` and only afterwards assigns `bunlers = insePoolBalance[RID-1]`, collapsing the claimant's insurance payout to zero.","impact":"The claimant who should receive the final residual insurance balance can be denied it entirely. Those insurance funds remain in the current round's main pool accounting and are redistributed elsewhere instead of paying the intended beneficiary.","paths":["Become a lucky insured PID from the previous round.","Be the claimant whose nominal `ticketInCost * 2` payout exceeds the remaining insurance balance.","Call `withdraw()` and hit the branch that zeros `insePoolBalance[RID-1]` before copying it into `bunlers`, causing a zero insurance payout."],"round":1,"source_agents":["codex_1"]}],"rejected_candidates":[]}
